4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE AWARD OF COSTS AND ATTORNEY FEES
5 BASED ON LEGISLATIVE CONDUCT; PROHIBITING LEGISLATIVE CONDUCT TO BE CONSIDERED IN A
6 BAD FAITH ANALYSIS; PROVIDING THAT LEGISLATIVE CONDUCT IS INADMISSIBLE FOR A BAD FAITH
7 ANALYSIS OR FOR AWARDING COSTS AND FEES; AMENDING SECTION 25-10-711, MCA; AND
8 PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND A RETROACTIVE APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 25-10-711, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "25-10-711. Award of costs against governmental government entity when suit or defense is
14 frivolous or pursued in bad faith -- legislative branch conduct not considered. (1) In Except as provided in
15 subsection (2), in any civil action brought by or against the state, a political subdivision, or an agency of the
16 state or a political subdivision, the opposing party, whether plaintiff or defendant, is entitled to the costs
17 enumerated in 25-10-201 and reasonable attorney fees as determined by the court if:
18 (a) the opposing party prevails against the state, political subdivision, or agency; and
19 (b) the court finds that the claim or defense of the state, political subdivision, or agency that
20 brought or defended the action was frivolous or pursued in bad faith.
21 (2) The conduct of the legislative branch in passing legislation may not be considered in a bad
22 faith analysis. This subsection applies to any award of costs or attorney fees against a government entity
23 regardless of whether the defense is frivolous or pursued in bad faith.
24 (3) Costs may be granted pursuant to subsection (1) notwithstanding any other provision of the law
25 to the contrary."
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Legislative conduct inadmissible. The conduct of the legislative
28 branch in passing legislation is not admissible in a bad faith analysis or for the purpose of awarding costs or
